 # Kali Linux VM Creation
## Initial Setup
1. Install the required ISO local machine
  - Navigated to https://www.kali.org/get-kali/#kali-installer-images
  - Installed kali-linux-2025.3-installer-amd64 ISO
2. Create the VM
  - selected the desired node for installation (devops-nitrogen)
  - Right click the chosen node and select create VM or go to top right and select create VM button
  - Proceed through the installation options:
    * General Tab
      - Select node (devops-nitrogen)
      - Select VM ID (1045)
      - Select Name for VM (MercerKali)
      - Select resource pool (Interns)
      - Click next    
    * OS Tab
      - Choose local storage and select the kali iso 
      - Click next
    * System Tab
      - Leave all options default and click next
    * Disk Tab
      - Leave Bus/Device default
      - Select local-lvm
      - Choose required storage space (50gb)
      - Click next
    * CPU Tab
      - Chose 1 socket
      - 4 cores 
      - type x86-64-v2-AES
      - Click next
    * Memory Tab
      - Select desired RAM (8192)
      - Click next
    * Network Tab
      - Changed bridge to vmbr0
      - Click next
    * Confirm Tab
      - Make sure it all looks correct and click confirm
## VM Installation/Config
1. Power on VM
  - Choose installation type (graphical install)
  - Pick language and location (English, U.S.)
  - Pick Keyboard type (American English)
  - Set hostname mercer-kali
  - Set Names/Password
  - Set clock
  - Partition Disks, used whole disk
  - Chose all files in one partition
  - Choose environment (xfce)








